SAPS spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane confirmed to MzansiLIVE at 4.30am that the baby &#8211; who was abducted on Friday &#8211; was found shortly after midnight on Saturday.A suspicious vehicle was searched at the Mariannhill Toll Plaza on the N3, and Siwaphiwe was found inside.&#8220;Baby found alive shortly after midnight. Three suspects arrested,&#8221; Zwane said via text message.More details are expected later in the morning.